# ShipKit CLI Project Overview

This project is a command-line tool built to install and manage shipkit.io and bones.sh instances. It uses [Clack](mdc:https:/www.clack.cc) for beautiful CLI prompts and interactions.

## Project Structure

- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Main project configuration
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration
- [src/](mdc:src) - Source code directory
  - [src/index.ts](mdc:src/index.ts) - Main entry point for the CLI
  - [src/types.ts](mdc:src/types.ts) - TypeScript type definitions
  - [src/utils.ts](mdc:src/utils.ts) - Utility functions
  - [src/commands/](mdc:src/commands) - Command implementations
- [bin/shipkit.js](mdc:bin/shipkit.js) - Executable CLI entry point

## Key Features

1. Install shipkit.io or bones.sh instances
2. List all managed instances
3. Remove instances
4. Update instances

## Build Process

The TypeScript source code is compiled to JavaScript in the `dist` directory using the TypeScript compiler. The compiled code is then executed via the bin/shipkit.js entry point.

## Configuration Storage

The CLI stores configuration data in the user's home directory at `~/.shipkit-cli/config.json`.
